
Ali's eyes wandered over to where the woman lay motionless. Sure enough, she held the piece of glass so firmly in her hand that it was drawing blood from her fingers and her palm. It was strange that her grip didn't loosen when she got knocked out.
"We should get going before any of those crazies crawl back out of that pit," Levi said. He stood up and Seto and Ali did the same.
When they turned in the direction they were initially heading, they ended up being face-to-face with the woman who Ali had kicked in the face. She just stood there, breathing heavily. Her face was angry, and it scared Ali. She looked at the woman's hand, and in it she held the hammer that had been dropped. Ali suddenly felt stupid for not picking it up.
"The mean man made me do it," the woman said through clenched teeth.